# OpenAI agents / orchestration

- Separate system, developer, tool, and task instructions intentionally.
- Define tools narrowly with bounded arguments and predictable outputs; avoid overlapping tools.
- Keep context relevant and bounded; prefer explicit handoffs when multiple agents or tools interact.
- Treat instruction, routing, and schema changes as behavior changes requiring targeted validation; prefer structured outputs when downstream depends on them.
